<h3>About CVS</h3>

<p>CVS is an old system for managing code.  In order to access a CVS repository, you must install a CVS client.</p>

<hr/>

<h3>Readonly Access Only</h3>
<p>SourceForge only supports readonly access to CVS now.
For more information see our
<a href="https://sourceforge.net/blog/decommissioning-cvs-for-commits/">blog post about decommissioning CVS commit support</a>.
</p>
<p>
If you are a project admin, you can <a href="https://sourceforge.net/p/forge/documentation/CVS/">convert your repository to SVN or Git with these instructions</a>.
</p>

<hr/>

<h3>Download</h3>
<p>You can download the complete repository in .zip format: <a href="https://sourceforge.net/code-snapshots/cvs/j/ju/junit.zip" rel="nofollow">https://sourceforge.net/code-snapshots/cvs/j/ju/junit.zip</a></p>
<p>Once you have downloaded the file you can unzip and checkout a working copy with the following command <code>cvs -d /full/path/to/junit co junit</code></p>


